  "title": "Present Tense — Regular Verbs",
  "titleEs": "El presente — verbos regulares",
  "icon": "✏️",
  "intro": "Spanish verbs come in three families: -AR, -ER, and -IR. Once you know the ending pattern for each family, you can conjugate thousands of verbs!",
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "rule",
      "title": "How conjugation works",
      "content": "Every Spanish verb has two parts:\n1. The STEM — remove the last two letters: hablar → habl-\n2. The ENDING — add the right ending for who is speaking\n\nThat's it! The ending tells you who is doing the action."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "title": "-AR verbs: HABLAR (to speak)",
      "headers": ["Pronoun", "Formula", "Result", "English"],
      "rows": [
        ["yo", "habl + o", "hablo", "I speak"],
        ["tú", "habl + as", "hablas", "you speak"],
        ["él / ella / Ud.", "habl + a", "habla", "he/she speaks"],
        ["nosotros", "habl + amos", "hablamos", "we speak"],
        ["vosotros (Spain)", "habl + áis", "habláis", "you all speak"],
        ["ellos / Uds.", "habl + an", "hablan", "they speak"]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "title": "-ER verbs: COMER (to eat)",
      "headers": ["Pronoun", "Formula", "Result", "English"],
      "rows": [
        ["yo", "com + o", "como", "I eat"],
        ["tú", "com + es", "comes", "you eat"],
        ["él / ella / Ud.", "com + e", "come", "he/she eats"],
        ["nosotros", "com + emos", "comemos", "we eat"],
        ["vosotros (Spain)", "com + éis", "coméis", "you all eat"],
        ["ellos / Uds.", "com + en", "comen", "they eat"]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "title": "-IR verbs: VIVIR (to live)",
      "headers": ["Pronoun", "Formula", "Result", "English"],
      "rows": [
        ["yo", "viv + o", "vivo", "I live"],
        ["tú", "viv + es", "vives", "you live"],
        ["él / ella / Ud.", "viv + e", "vive", "he/she lives"],
        ["nosotros", "viv + imos", "vivimos", "we live"],
        ["vosotros (Spain)", "viv + ís", "vivís", "you all live"],
        ["ellos / Uds.", "viv + en", "viven", "they live"]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "examples",
      "title": "Common regular verbs",
      "items": [
        { "es": "Hablo español todos los días.", "en": "I speak Spanish every day.", "note": "hablar → hablo (yo)" },
        { "es": "¿Dónde vives tú?", "en": "Where do you live?", "note": "vivir → vives (tú)" },
        { "es": "Ellos comen a las dos.", "en": "They eat at two o'clock.", "note": "comer → comen (ellos)" }
      ]
    }
